{
  "winner": "candidate_a",
  "candidate_a_score": 72,
  "candidate_b_score": 45,
  "rationale": "Candidate A correctly replaces the Gemini backend with a local rule-based engine, adds a canvas-based audio visualizer, and implements a typewriter effect that scrolls the chat panel. However, it introduces a transient UI bug where the full response appears instantly in the message history while the typewriter overlay renders below it, and it omits the typewriter effect on the initial welcome message. Candidate B also implements the backend and visualizer, but its typewriter integration is critically broken: the chat history is populated with an empty placeholder that is never updated with the final text, so the response disappears once typing finishes; the welcome-message typewriter is also invisible. Because Candidate A preserves message history and delivers a functional (if imperfect) user experience, it is the better patch."
}

